<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1677,1884]" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">
<emphasis box="[189,253,1678,1703]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. L. Luo, J. K Liu, H. Y. Su &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2016" box="[289,581,1677,1703]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Morosphaeriaceae" genus="Helicascus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chiangraiensis">
<emphasis box="[289,581,1677,1703]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Helicascus chiangraiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected from decaying wood submerged in a pond in 
<collectingRegion box="[1218,1447,1677,1703]" country="Thailand" name="Chiang Rai" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Chiang Rai Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[136,239,1713,1739]" name="Thailand" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. According to the key provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang, H. &amp; Hyde, K. D. &amp; Abdel-Wahab, M. A. &amp; Abdel-Aziz, F. A. &amp; Ariyawansa, H. A. &amp; KoKo, T. W. &amp; Zhao, R. L. &amp; Alias, S. A. &amp; Bahkali, A. H. &amp; Zhou, D. Q." box="[635,855,1713,1740]" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" pagination="147 - 166" refId="ref7042" refString="Zhang, H., Hyde, K. D., Abdel-Wahab, M. A., Abdel-Aziz, F. A., Ariyawansa, H. A., KoKo, T. W., Zhao, R. L., Alias, S. A., Bahkali, A. H. &amp; Zhou, D. Q. (2013) A modern concept for Helicascus with a Pleurophomopsis-like asexual state. Sydowia 65 (1): 147 - 166." type="journal article" year="2013">
Zhang 
<emphasis box="[714,763,1713,1739]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">et al</emphasis>
. (2013)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. L. Luo, J. K Liu, H. Y. Su &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2016" box="[867,1066,1713,1739]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Morosphaeriaceae" genus="Helicascus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chiangraiensis">
<emphasis box="[867,1066,1713,1739]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">H. chiangraiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1214,1382,1714,1739]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Morosphaeriaceae" genus="Helicascus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aegyptiacus">
<emphasis box="[1214,1382,1714,1739]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">H. aegyptiacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its coiled endoascus, verruculose ascospores surrounded by a gelatinous sheath and both are collected from freshwater habitats. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. L. Luo, J. K Liu, H. Y. Su &amp; K. D. Hyde" authorityYear="2016" box="[352,550,1785,1811]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Morosphaeriaceae" genus="Helicascus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chiangraiensis">
<emphasis box="[352,550,1785,1811]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">H. chiangraiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[696,864,1786,1811]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Morosphaeriaceae" genus="Helicascus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aegyptiacus">
<emphasis box="[696,864,1786,1811]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">H. aegyptiacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having unilocular, smaller ascostromata, while 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Morosphaeriaceae" genus="Helicascus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="4" pageNumber="186" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aegyptiacus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="186">H. aegyptiacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a longer ascostromata, pseudostromata with 2–3(4) dark locules (
<tableCitation box="[1053,1141,1821,1847]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,224,159,183]" captionText="TABLE 2. Habitat and morphological comparison among species of Helicascus (data from Kohlmeyer 1969, Hyde 1991, Shearer 1993, Zhang et al. 2013, 2014, 2015)." pageId="4" pageNumber="186">Table 2</tableCitation>
). In addition, the molecular analysis also showed that these two species are phylogenetically distinct from each other.
</paragraph>
